    "---\n",
    "## 5. Algorithm 1 — TF-IDF Cosine Similarity\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\text{cosine}(\\vec{q}, \\vec{d_i}) = \\frac{\\vec{q} \\cdot \\vec{d_i}}{\\|\\vec{q}\\| \\cdot \\|\\vec{d_i}\\|}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Steps:** build query → transform to same space → cosine with all jobs → rank → scale to [40, 99] → rank-0 boost.\n",
    "\n",
    "Semantic advantage: bigrams like `machine learning` and `natural language` are single features, so a profile with `NLP` can still match jobs listing `natural language processing`."
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "s5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\n",
    "\n",
    "def recommend_tfidf(user, jobs, vectorizer, tfidf_matrix, top_n=10):\n",
    "    query_vec = vectorizer.transform([build_user_profile_text(user)])\n",
    "    sims = cosine_similarity(query_vec, tfidf_matrix).flatten()\n",
    "    top_idx = np.argsort(sims)[::-1][:top_n]\n",
    "    results = []\n",
    "    for rank, idx in enumerate(top_idx):\n",
    "        job = dict(jobs[idx])\n",
    "        raw = float(sims[idx])\n",
    "        score = int(min(99, max(40, round(raw * 200))))\n",
    "        if rank == 0 and score < 85:\n",
    "            score = min(99, score + 20)\n",
    "        job['match_score'] = score\n",
    "        job['raw_cosine'] = round(raw, 4)\n",
    "        job['algo'] = 'TF-IDF'\n",
    "        results.append(job)\n",
    "    return results\n",
    "\n",
    "USERS = [\n",
    "    {'name':'Alex Chen',      'title':'AI Specialist',        'experience_years':6,\n",
